articles.description: Boston College won its first road game in Atlantic Coast Conference play in nearly three years with an 81-58 victory over Pittsburgh on Tuesday.
articles.headline: Boston College tops Pitt 81-58 for elusive ACC road win

articles.description: Marcus Derrickson tied a career-high with 27 points, on 11-of-13 shooting, for his eighth 20-plus point game this season and Georgetown beat Butler 87-83 on Tuesday night.
articles.headline: Georgetown snaps 4-game road losing streak, tops Butler

articles.description: Jeff Dowtin hits a trailing Jared Terrell who drills a 3-pointer for the Rams in the first half.

articles.description: Third-ranked Villanova will begin a difficult stretch of playing four of its next five games on the road with a trip to Providence Wednesday night at the Dunkin Donuts Center.
articles.headline: Freshmen send No. 3 Villanova surging into Providence

videos.description: Oklahoma's Trae Young finds Rashard Odomes in transition for the easy basket.
videos.headline: Young's vision leads to transition basket

videos.description: Oklahoma's Trae Young splits the defenders and connects with Khadeem Lattin for the dunk.
videos.headline: Young uses the bounce pass to perfection

videos.description: Oklahoma's Rashard Odomes gets the steal and finishes with the double clutch dunk on the fastbreak.
videos.headline: Odomes with the steal and dunk

videos.description: Oklahoma's Trae Young puts up the shot well behind the arc to drain the 3-pointer as Oklahoma takes on Baylor.
videos.headline: Young hits the deep three

videos.description: Oklahoma's Trae Young drills another 3-pointer from Steph Curry range to help spark the Sooners' offense.
videos.headline: Young drains another deep three

videos.description: Oklahoma's Trae Young runs the pick and roll with Khadeem Lattin, who finishes strong at the rim with the two-handed dunk.
videos.headline: Young runs the pick  and roll to perfection

videos.description: Oklahoma's Trae Young puts the ball on a string to get it to Khadeem Lattin who gets the basket and draws the foul.
videos.headline: Young makes it look easy

videos.description: Oklahoma's Trae Young goes coast-to-coast and finishes underneath with the left-handed layup.
videos.headline: Young does it all by himself

videos.description: Oklahoma head coach Lon Kruger speaks on how the Sooners' offense and defense can support Trae Young's dynamic night against Baylor.
videos.headline: Kruger: 'We need to do more around Trae'

videos.description: 6'-2" Trae Young knocks down the 3-pointer over Baylor's Jo Lual-Acuil Jr., who is 7'-0 tall.
videos.headline: Young hits the 3-pointer over the seven footer

videos.description: Oklahoma's Trae Young shows off his ball-handling skills and finishes with the one-handed floater in the paint.
videos.headline: Young's handles lead to floater

videos.description: Oklahoma's Trae Young hits another deep 3-pointer against Baylor.
videos.headline: Young continues to show off his range

videos.description: Oklahoma's Trae Young continues to show off his deep shooting ability by draining the deep 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Young does it again

videos.description: Oklahoma's Trae Young makes another 3-pointer from deep and gets the off-balance layup to go.
videos.headline: Young continues 'sensational' performance

videos.description: Oklahoma's Trae Young collects the deflected ball, makes a move and banks in the shot as the Sooners battle with Baylor.
videos.headline: Young continues highlight performance

videos.description: After a missed 3-pointer, Baylor's King McClure puts up the desperation shot and the Bears come up short against the Sooners.
videos.headline: Baylor misses at the buzzer

videos.description: Oklahoma's Trae Young speaks on how he felt like he was in a shooting rhythm against Baylor.
videos.headline: Young on hot shooting: 'Like shooting into an ocean'

videos.description: Trae Young's fourth 40-plus-point game of the season lifts Oklahoma to a 98-96 victory over Baylor.
videos.headline: Young goes off for 44 in Sooners' win
